sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OIDC as OIDC Issuer<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant App as Upstream Application<br/>8081/TCP HTTP (localhost)
    participant Prometheus as prometheus-k8s<br/>(openshift-monitoring)

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,App: Flow 1: Bearer Token Authentication (TokenReview)
        Client->>Proxy: HTTPS POST /api/v1/resource<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: TokenReview Response<br/>(authenticated=true, user, groups)
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authorization.k8s.io/v1/subjectaccessreviews<br/>resourceAttributes from config
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: SubjectAccessReview Response<br/>(allowed=true)
        Proxy->>App: HTTP POST /api/v1/resource<br/>Headers: x-remote-user, x-remote-groups<br/>(localhost, no TLS)
        App-->>Proxy: HTTP 200 Response
        Proxy-->>Client: HTTPS 200 Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Client,OIDC: Flow 2: OIDC JWT Authentication
        Client->>Proxy: HTTPS POST /api/v1/resource<br/>Auth: Bearer OIDC-JWT
        Proxy->>OIDC: GET /.well-known/openid-configuration<br/>GET /keys (JWKS)
        OIDC-->>Proxy: JWKS Response (signing keys)
        Note over Proxy: Validate JWT signature,<br/>issuer, audience.<br/>Map claims → user/groups
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authorization.k8s.io/v1/subjectaccessreviews<br/>user/groups from JWT claims
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: SubjectAccessReview Response<br/>(allowed=true)
        Proxy->>App: HTTP POST /api/v1/resource<br/>(localhost)
        App-->>Proxy: HTTP 200 Response
        Proxy-->>Client: HTTPS 200 Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over Prometheus,App: Flow 3: Prometheus Metrics Scrape (Hardcoded Allow)
        Prometheus->>Proxy: HTTPS GET /metrics<br/>Auth: Bearer SA Token
        Note over Proxy: Hardcoded authorizer:<br/>system:serviceaccount:<br/>openshift-monitoring:prometheus-k8s<br/>→ Allow (bypasses SAR)
        Proxy->>App: HTTP GET /metrics<br/>(localhost)
        App-->>Proxy: HTTP 200 (Prometheus metrics)
        Proxy-->>Prometheus: HTTPS 200 (metrics)
    end
